<item>
            <title>[CXF-3143] SOAPBindingUtil &apos;leaks&apos; proxy classes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-3143</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;org.apache.cxf.tools.util.SOAPBindingUtil.getProxy(Class&amp;lt;T&amp;gt;, Object) creates proxies in the same class loader as the class it is proxying.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This essentially leaks them,  since the classes being proxied are prone to be in the system class loader, but the proxies are being created on behalf of the current thread.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The simplest improvement is to create them in the context class loader, so that (for example) the wsdl2java mojo can arrange for them to be GC-ed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another interesting question is whether there should be some sort of cache: it seems to me that we&apos;re creating proxies for the same IBM WSDL soap binding impl class over and over.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
